cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on video analysis and activity recognition, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed Temporal Relation Network (TRN) is a neural network module designed to reason about temporal dependencies between video frames, which involves learning and reasoning about complex relationships between objects or entities over time. This requires a certain level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper evaluates the TRN-equipped networks on three video datasets, which involves multimedia computing (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for video captioning and description.
